cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.DC, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the integration of ICN, C-RAN, and SDN for HetNets, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper may involve information theory concepts related to data transmission and processing in the proposed system. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with the integration of different communication technologies for HetNets, which is a core area of communications and networking. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed system may involve distributed computing and processing of data in the cloud or edge servers. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper may involve the design and implementation of hardware components for the proposed system, such as ICN routers and C-RAN base stations.
